    <main class="policy__main">
      <section class="policy-section" id="how-to-measure">
        <h2 class="policy-section__title">How to measure</h2>
        <p>You&rsquo;ll need a soft tape measure and someone to help. Measure over your underwear, not over thick layers.</p>
         <ul class="policy-list">
           <li><strong>Bust</strong> — Around the fullest part, with the tape level across your back.</li>
           <li><strong>Waist</strong> — The narrowest part of your torso, usually just above the navel.</li>
           <li><strong>Hips</strong> — The fullest part of your hips, usually 20cm below the waist.</li>
           <li><strong>Inseam</strong> — From the crotch seam down to where you want the trouser to end.</li>
         </ul>
         <p>If you&rsquo;re between sizes, size up — our fabrics rarely have stretch, and we&rsquo;d rather you have room than feel tight.</p>
      </section>

